      "content": "**4. Enforcement and Consequences**  \nThe policy employs a tiered consequence system to address violations and encourage compliance.  \n\n* **Tier 1 – First Offense**: For a first-time violation of this policy, the student will receive a written warning and a brief note in their grade book. The teacher will also be notified to monitor the student’s phone usage during the next two weeks.  \n* **Tier 2 – Repeat Offense**: If a student repeats the violation, they will receive a formal reprimand, a short suspension from the next day’s class, and a parent notification letter.  \n* **Tier 3 – Persistent Misuse**: For continued or repeated violations, the student will be issued a disciplinary report, a mandatory parent conference, and a temporary restriction on phone use during the next semester.  \n\n* **Secret Usage**: Any student found using a phone secretly—whether it is hidden under a desk, in a pocket, or in a bag—will be treated as a violation. The teacher will log the incident, and the student will be subject to the same tiered consequences as above. In cases of secret usage, the teacher will also review the phone’s battery life and data plan to ensure it does not interfere",
